    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix pthread error handling in time_manager library\n\n### Summary\nThe time_manager library in common/utils was using DevAssert() for pthread function return values, causing the entire program to crash when pthread operations failed. This was particularly problematic in the unlock() function where a simple EPERM error would terminate the process.\n\nThe fix replaces all DevAssert() calls with proper error logging that allows the program to continue execution while still reporting the error conditions. This provides better diagnostic information and prevents unexpected crashes.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/time_manager/time_source.c`: Replaced DevAssert() with error logging in all pthread wrapper functions (init_mutex, init_cond, lock, unlock, condwait, condsignal, wait_thread_termination)\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the original issue:\n1. Run any application using the time_manager library\n2. Force a pthread_mutex_unlock() failure by attempting to unlock a mutex not owned by the current thread\n3. Observe the program crash with an assertion failure instead of graceful error handling\n\nWith the fix, the same scenario will log detailed error information to stderr but allow the program to continue execution.\n"
}